                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>\n                <date>June 10<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1862</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dr Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">You must not think me<lb/> neglectful in not having written to you\n                before<lb/> this. Many things at times prevent me from <lb/>writing at the time and\n                then it passes over.<lb/> No doubt ere this you have received a Letter<lb/> from\n                    <persName>Mr Myers</persName> and with it the receipt signed<lb/> by me of the\n                Books he placed in my possession<lb/> on sale for you. I shall try and do my\n                best<lb/> to dispose of them for you. The prices here are<lb/> too high there are so\n                few buyers, please let<lb/> me know positively the lowest price at which<lb/> I may\n                sell, so that I can act safely and I<lb/> will do all I can. I hope you received\n                my<lb/> parcel by <persName>Rabbi Nissan</persName> if you can send me<lb/> any more\n                of the Back Nos for which I wrote<lb/> you will oblige me, at the same time\n                have<lb/> you any whole <hi rend=\"underline\">Nos</hi> as 1-2-3-4-5-6-7-8<lb/> I have\n                none of these Vols. I should like to have<lb/> them either bound or unbound I shall\n                then<lb/> be the only <hi rend=\"underline\">one</hi> in the <placeName>Pacific\n                    Coast</placeName> who will<lb/> have a regular file of them. Of course I\n                will</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3vt1h90n/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
