              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3vt1h90n/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>Many here surmise that I inform you of<lb/> all that passes—but I do not wish my\n                name<lb/> to appear for many reasons—especially as<lb/> some of my members and other\n                of the <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> are friends to the Gleaner, and have pity on the poor\n                old man as they call him x<lb/> that encourages him in all his doings—<lb/> I shall\n                still inform you of all that passes<lb/> because I do think that ultimately by\n                so<lb/> doing we shall in time affect some good<lb/> In the pulpit I speak of these\n                things fearlessly<lb/> I will send you a sermon I preached on<lb/> the <date>1<hi\n                        rend=\"sup\">st</hi></date> day <add>Hebrew</add> by which you will see<lb/>\n                that I do as I say and act upon the principle<lb/>\n                <add>Hebrew</add>. <persName>Eckman</persName> does all he can to<lb/> injure me in\n                the minds of the people as<lb/> my Election is only from year to year but<lb/> I\n                tell my folks that my <add>Hebrew</add> is in God x<lb/> not in man, even the\n                Reformers hold<lb/> me in respect altho' I tell them of their<lb/> wrongs.\n                    <sic>even</sic>\n                <persName>Dr Cohn</persName> will not do such<lb/> things as these men do. He works\n                hard with<lb/> me to get the people to keep <add>Hebrew</add> . I have<lb/>\n                succeeded in one or two instances and I hope<lb/> in time we shall do more—but it is\n                very difficult<lb/> the Dollars &amp; cents are the main thing with<lb/> our people\n                here—still we must do our duty</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3vt1h90n/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
