                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">/5</p>\n            <p><add>Hebrew</add>. And read the <add>Hebrew</add> in the<lb/> old Orthodox Style to a\n                crowded auditory<lb/> which gave great satisfaction. I still and<lb/> will adhere to\n                our good old times and<lb/> will suffer no innovation, and I am happy<lb/> to say\n                that with few exceptions my <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> support me in this respect,\n                altho' at<lb/> times I have to go into the Battle field<lb/> but I will and do not\n                flinch. The Gleaner<lb/> being the only Jewish Organ here sometimes<lb/> rouses up\n                one or two who go abroad<lb/> and say this is old and out of tune and<lb/> that\n                causes mischief. I heed them not<lb/> and when I reason with them they are<lb/>\n                silenced. I am so far fortunate that the<lb/> Board of Trustees tho' individually\n                not<lb/> very ultra Orthodox yet they will not allow<lb/> any one to interfere with\n                me in the synagogue<lb/> service, at the head of them is our <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                an Englishman who has held office for<lb/> many years who is really a stanch\n                    <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> and who never neglects to be in<lb/>\n                <add>Hebrew</add> whenever service is performed<lb/> our <add>Hebrew</add> is opened\n                every <add>Hebrew</add> and<lb/> three times an <add>Hebrew</add> and there you\n                find<lb/> the <add>Hebrew</add> at his port and this has a</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3vt1h90n/canvas/p5"
                }
              ]
